docs\design\2026-04-27-behavioral-metrics-design.md:535:**Decision:** v1 accepts only synchronous 
`Iterable<SessionBundle>`. Arrays, generators, sets, and any custom synchronous iterable work. `AsyncIterable` is NOT 
supported.
docs\design\2026-04-27-behavioral-metrics-design.md:537:**Rationale:** Spec 3's harness is synchronous; the natural 
composition is synchronous corpus reduction. `AsyncIterable` is worth the complexity when corpus loading involves I/O 
- Spec 7's bundle index, network-backed corpora - none of which exist yet. Adding async now is 
abstraction-before-pressure. The future-compat path is a separate `runMetricsAsync` function (returns 
`Promise<MetricsResult>`), not an overload of `runMetrics` - overloading would force the return type to widen to 
`MetricsResult | Promise<MetricsResult>`, which IS breaking for existing callers that assume sync. Two named functions 
keeps the v1 surface stable.
